			<item>
				<title>Opinionated Software</title>
				<link>http://localhost:1313/blog/post/opinionated-software/</link>
				<pubDate>Sat, 13 Jun 2026 15:53:51 -0400</pubDate>
				<guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/post/opinionated-software/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;This one hits close to home these days&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Opinionated software, or software pre-configured with behaviours strongly-suggested (if not outright forced), can be great!&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s when the user of the tool and the tool-maker disagree that opinionated software can be&amp;hellip; not so great&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I like to think that I&amp;rsquo;m a pretty easygoing guy, but sometimes I run against the grain when it comes to the way my tools would prefer that I work.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
